            <title>[SPARK-9886] Validate usages of Runtime.getRuntime.addShutdownHook</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-9886</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;While refactoring calls to Utils.addShutdownHook to spark ShutdownHookManager in PR #8109, I&apos;ve seen instances of calls to Runtime.getRuntime.addShutdownHook:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;org\apache\spark\deploy\ExternalShuffleService.scala:126&lt;br/&gt;
org\apache\spark\deploy\mesos\MesosClusterDispatcher.scala:113&lt;br/&gt;
org\apache\spark\storage\ExternalBlockStore.scala:181&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Comment from @vanzin:&lt;br/&gt;
&quot;From a quick look, it seems that at least the one in ExternalBlockStore should be changed; the other two seem to be separate processes (i.e. they are not part of a Spark application) so that&apos;s questionable. But I&apos;d say leave it for a different change (maybe file a separate bug so it doesn&apos;t fall through the cracks).&quot;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
